    dc:title "Review of the millipede tribe Polydrepanini, with the description of a new species from Kerala state, southern India (Diplopoda, Polydesmida, Paradoxosomatidae, Alogolykinae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709518>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709524>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709546>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709548>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709552>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709550> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709518>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9–12. Polydrepanum horridum Golovatch, 1984. Right gonopod, lateral, dorsal, mesal and ventral views, respectively.After Golovatch (1984). Abbreviations: a, apicolateral spine; k, basal loop of solenomere; lo, mesal lobe; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Scale bar: 0.4 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5709518/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709524>
    dc:description "FIGURES 16–20. Polydrepanum tamilum Carl, 1932. 16. Male leg 2, lateral view. 17. Entire left gonopod, mesal view. 18. Distal half of left gonopod, lateral view. 19. Entire right gonopod, mesal view. 20. Distal half of right gonopod, sublateral view. 16–18: after Carl (1932); 19, 20: after Jeekel (1980b). Abbreviations: a and b, dorsal distofemoral processes; ad, adenostyle; lo, lateral protecting lobe/shield; k, basal loop of solenomere; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Drawn not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5709524/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709546>
    dc:description "FIGURES 42–44. Delarthrum longisetum (Golovatch, 1994) (= Parorthomorpha longiseta Golovatch, 1994). 42. Entire left gonopod, mesal view. 43, 44. Distal half of left gonopod, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. After Golovatch (1994a). Abbreviations: sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5709546/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709548>
    dc:description "FIGURES 45, 46. Dasypharkis rugulosa (Carl, 1932) (= Orthomorpha rugulosa Carl, 1932). Entire left (45) and right (46) gonopod, mesal and lateral views, respectively. After Jeekel (1980b). Abbreviations: a, lateral distofemoral spine; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Drawn not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5709548/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709552>
    dc:description "FIGURES 52, 53. Polydrepanum granuliferum (Attems, 1936) (= Sundanina granulifera Attems, 1936). Entire right gonopod, lateral and mesal views, respectively.After Golovatch (1984). Abbreviations: a, mesal distofemoral spine; b, lateral distofemoral spine; k, basal loop of solenomere; lo, lateral protecting lobe; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5709552/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709550>
    dc:description "FIGURES 47–51. Polydrepanum lamprum (Chamberlin, 1920) (= Orthomorpha lampra Chamberlin, 1920). 47. Entire right gonopod, mesal view. 48, 49. Distal half of right gonopod, sublateral and mesal views, respectively. 50. Entire left gonopod, mesal view. 51. Distal half of left gonopod, ventral view. 47–49: after Jeekel (1972);: 50, 51: after Carl (1932). Abbreviations: a, mesal distofemoral spine; b, lateral distofemoral spine; c, ventromesal distofemoral process; k, basal loop of solenomere; lo, lateral protecting lobe; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Drawn not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5709550/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

